Function

While defining a function we should counsider identifier's rules

we cannot use the values inside the functions outside the function

def is used

def function_name(parameters) #defining function

function name(arguement)#calling functional

types of argument :

1)positional argument
    the values in the argument must be supplied according to the position of the parameter.
    the number of arguement must be equal to the number of parameters
    WE CANNOT REPEAT THE DEFINED PARAMETER MULTIPLE TIMES IN SAME 
    eg 
    def add(a,b,b) 
2)keyword argument
    we must pass the argument with key and value pair
    The parameters name and the argument name must be same

    eg
    def add(a,b):return a+b
    add(a=10,b=20) 

3)default argument
    add(a,b=10):

    in this arguement the value is defined in the parameter as defiled value
    if we supply value of a. Funtion doesnt give error without the actual value of b\\

    def add(b=10,a)X we should not weite positional arguement before keyword arguemrnt



4)Variable length

it is used when we wnt unlimited no of input from ser
must add(a,*c)â™¥
    add(*c,a)X

the datatype of the variable will be tuple
this rule also applies to Keyword variable length

5)Keyword varianle length
stoerd as dictionary

